It is a basically brand new Nikon Monarch 5-20x44mm Side Focus / Bullet Drop Compensator reticle.  You match the BDC reticle with Nikon's amazing Spot-On ballistic software - you simply log onto their website OR use their mobile app ... input your data- Put your caliber, your brand of ammo, your exact load (For example- my ProStaff 4-12x40mm on my Savage .22LR - i might input .22LR, and then select CCI, and go to the exact load, say Mini Mags 40gr RN , ) then you select your exact scope model, and your range of zero and range to target. I have a Winchester Model 94AE (angle eject) in .30-30 that I'm trying to turn into a bolt gun for a deer hunting youngster. 

This is a newer model (Serial puts it in the early 90's) with the crossbolt push safety, and it has the factory scope holes pre-drilled for mounts, but just the open sights on it for now. I bought it used as my first deer gun but haven't used it for years other than take it out once a year and wipe it down with an oily rag. Original wood stock, one poorly drilled sling stud hole in the butt that's been filled with wood putty and sanded smooth...otherwise in pretty darn nice shape.

I'm looking for a MN deer rifle, preferably with open sights, but also something I wouldn't feel bad about eventually mounting a scope to. Something in 7.62x39...or possibly a later Savage Model 340 (with the pre-drilled scope mount holes) in .30-30...or sporterized .303 or .30-06.
